Brundisium on the l7th of March: that Caesar on the next day entered the town, made a speech and went off at full speed to Rome, meaning to be at the city before the lst of April, to remain there a few days and then to set out for Spain. It seemed proper since we had sure news of Caesar’s approach to send your servants back to you to give informa- tion as early as possible. Your charges have our attention, and we will act as circumstances demand. Trebatius is trying hard to reach you before Caesar.

XVI

CICERO To ATTICUS, GREETING.
